ce:section.ce:para:
As shown in Fig. S3-A and B, under the same concentration, Fe3+, Icariin and Rifampin slightly quenches the fluorescence of B-NSCDs, while morin can almost completely quench the fluorescence, which indicates that B-NSCDs have an obvious and effective response to morin. In order to explore whether other coexisting substances can interfere with the quenching effect of morin, competition experiments were conducted. It can be observed from Figs. S3–C that the orange bars represent the fluorescence response (F/F

                           0
                        ) of B-NSCDs to various substances. When adding 100 μM of morin (green bars), the quenching degree is the same. To investigate the maximum tolerable multiples of competing substances (the concentration of morin with an error of no more than ± 5%), increasing the concentration of coexisting substances was implemented, as shown in Table S4, which denotes that the coexisting substances will not interfere with the fluorescence quenching. B-NSCDs have a rapid response to morin, and the fluorescence quenching rate can reach more than 80% in only 30 s (Figs. S3–D). It shows that the low concentration B-NSCDs obtained by concentration adjustment have sensitive selectivity, outstanding anti-interference ability and superior time response.
